window._qaValidationHTML = "<div class=\"methodology-hero\">\n<div class=\"methodology-hero-inner\">\n<h2 class=\"methodology-hero-title\">QA Validation Report</h2>\n<p class=\"methodology-hero-subtitle\">\nIndependent Verification of Scanner Traceability and Accuracy\n</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"card mb-lg\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<h3 class=\"help-section-title\">Purpose</h3>\n<p class=\"help-section-desc\">\nThis report provides independent, automated verification that the FedRAMP Cloud Compliance Scanner \ncorrectly implements what it claims. For FedRAMP Assessors (3PAOs) evaluating automated \nassessment tools, trust requires proof  - not just documentation. This validation \nstatically analyzes the scanner&rsquo;s configuration files and Python source code to verify \nthe entire traceability chain:\n</p>\n<div class=\"help-traceability-chain\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-step\" data-step=\"1\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-number\">1</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-content\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-title\">FedRAMP Baseline</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-desc\">Low / Moderate / High authorization level</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-step\" data-step=\"2\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-number\">2</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-content\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-title\">NIST 800-53 Rev 5 Control</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-desc\">One of 2068 security requirements</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-step\" data-step=\"3\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-number\">3</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-content\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-title\">800-53A Assessment Objective</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-desc\">Specific \"determine if\" statement</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-step\" data-step=\"4\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-number\">4</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-content\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-title\">Scanner Check Definition</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-desc\">JSON config with check_id, api_call, expected</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-step\" data-step=\"5\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-number\">5</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-content\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-title\">Scanner Python Method</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-desc\">Actual code that calls cloud APIs</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-step\" data-step=\"6\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-number\">6</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-content\">\n<div class=\"help-chain-title\">Compliance Determination</div>\n<div class=\"help-chain-desc\">Met / Not Met / Manual Review</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"help-section-desc\">\nThe validation runs <strong>10 QA checks</strong> across two tiers: config validation (checks 1&ndash;8) \nverifies the integrity and completeness of the check definitions, and scanner logic validation \n(checks 9&ndash;10) verifies that the Python code matches what the config describes. \nNo cloud credentials are required  - this is purely static analysis.\n</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"card mb-lg\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<h3 class=\"help-section-title\">Validation Scope  - What Is Tested and Why</h3>\n<p class=\"help-section-desc\">\nThe 10 QA checks are organized into two tiers. <strong>Config Validation</strong> (QA 1.1&ndash;1.8) \nanalyzes the JSON check definitions and NIST control mappings. <strong>Scanner Logic Validation</strong> \n(QA 2.1&ndash;2.2) uses Python AST analysis to verify the actual scanner source code matches the config.\n</p>\n<table class=\"data-table\">\n<thead><tr>\n<th style=\"width:60px\">QA #</th>\n<th style=\"width:80px\">Tier</th>\n<th style=\"width:200px\">Check Name</th>\n<th>What It Verifies</th>\n<th>Why It Matters</th>\n</tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.1</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Structural Integrity</strong></td>\n<td>Every check definition in <code>config/checks/*.json</code> contains all required fields: <code>check_id</code>, <code>name</code>, <code>service</code>, <code>api_call</code>, <code>expected</code>, <code>severity</code>, and <code>supports_objectives</code>.</td>\n<td>Prevents runtime errors from malformed check definitions and ensures every check has complete metadata for reports.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.2</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Objective Cross-Reference</strong></td>\n<td>Every <code>supports_objectives</code> entry in a check references an objective ID that actually exists in <code>nist_800_53_controls.json</code>.</td>\n<td>Guarantees that check-to-objective mappings are valid  - no check claims to support a non-existent assessment objective.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.3</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Coverage Completeness</strong></td>\n<td>Every automatable assessment objective is either covered by an automated check or flagged as requiring documentation.</td>\n<td>Ensures no automatable objective falls through the cracks  - every one is addressed by a check or documentation requirement.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.4</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Method Mapping</strong></td>\n<td>Every <code>check_id</code> in config has a corresponding entry in <code>engine.py</code>&rsquo;s <code>*_CHECK_METHODS</code> dictionaries that maps it to a scanner method name.</td>\n<td>Confirms the scan engine knows which Python method to call for each check. Unmapped checks run as &ldquo;not yet implemented.&rdquo;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.5</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-manual\">Scanner</span></td>\n<td><strong>Method Existence</strong></td>\n<td>Every method name referenced in <code>*_CHECK_METHODS</code> actually exists as a <code>check_*</code> method in the corresponding scanner class.</td>\n<td>Prevents runtime <code>AttributeError</code>s  - every wired-up check has a real implementation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.6</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Check ID Format</strong></td>\n<td>All <code>check_id</code> values match the pattern <code>{family}-{control}[-{enhancement}]-{provider}-{seq}</code> (e.g., <code>ac-2-aws-001</code>, <code>ac-6-3-azure-001</code>).</td>\n<td>Ensures consistent, parseable identifiers across all check definitions for reporting and traceability.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.7</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Control Completeness</strong></td>\n<td>All base NIST 800-53 Rev 5 controls from <code>nist_800_53_controls.json</code> appear in <code>config/checks/*.json</code> (either as automated checks or manual-only entries).</td>\n<td>Guarantees full NIST 800-53 Rev 5 coverage  - no base control is omitted from the check configuration.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.8</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Provider Parity</strong></td>\n<td>Every automated control has checks defined for all three cloud providers (AWS, Azure, GCP).</td>\n<td>Ensures consistent assessment coverage regardless of which cloud platform the client uses.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>2.1</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-manual\">Scanner</span></td>\n<td><strong>API Call Match</strong></td>\n<td>The <code>api_call</code> field in each check&rsquo;s config matches the actual cloud API calls found in the scanner Python code (via AST analysis and delegation resolution).</td>\n<td>Confirms the scanner actually calls the APIs it documents  - no hidden behavior, no dead config.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>2.2</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-manual\">Scanner</span></td>\n<td><strong>Expected Condition Match</strong></td>\n<td>Key terms from the config <code>expected</code> field appear in the scanner method&rsquo;s source code (heuristic fuzzy match).</td>\n<td>Supplementary check that the code&rsquo;s validation logic aligns with the documented expected condition. Warnings are informational only (see explanation below).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"card mb-lg\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<h3 class=\"help-section-title\">Validation Results</h3>\n<div class=\"help-stats-grid\">\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"total\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">496</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">Cloud Checks</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">config definitions</div></div>\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"controls\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">2068</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">Controls</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">NIST 800-53 Rev 5</div></div>\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"objectives\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">3</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">CSPs</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">AWS + Azure + GCP</div></div>\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"automated\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">3743</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">Validations</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">individual tests</div></div>\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"manual\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">10/10</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">QA Checks</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">passing</div></div>\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"total\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">0</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">Errors</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">blocking issues</div></div>\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"azure\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">66</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">Warnings</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">informational</div></div>\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"gcp\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">PASS</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">Result</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">overall</div></div>\n</div>\n<table class=\"data-table mt-md\">\n<thead><tr>\n<th style=\"width:40px\">#</th>\n<th style=\"width:80px\">Tier</th>\n<th>QA Check</th>\n<th style=\"width:70px\">Pass</th>\n<th style=\"width:70px\">Fail</th>\n<th style=\"width:70px\">Warn</th>\n<th style=\"width:80px\">Status</th>\n</tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.1</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Structural Integrity</strong></td>\n<td>496</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">PASS</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.2</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Objective Cross-Reference</strong></td>\n<td>496</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">PASS</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.3</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Coverage Completeness</strong></td>\n<td>145</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>31</td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">PASS</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.4</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Method Mapping</strong></td>\n<td>495</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">PASS</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.5</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-manual\">Scanner</span></td>\n<td><strong>Method Existence</strong></td>\n<td>493</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">PASS</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.6</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Check ID Format</strong></td>\n<td>496</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">PASS</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.7</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Control Completeness</strong></td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">PASS</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1.8</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">Config</span></td>\n<td><strong>Provider Parity</strong></td>\n<td>100</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">PASS</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>2.1</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-manual\">Scanner</span></td>\n<td><strong>API Call Match</strong></td>\n<td>495</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">PASS</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>2.2</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-manual\">Scanner</span></td>\n<td><strong>Expected Condition Match</strong></td>\n<td>461</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>34</td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">PASS</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"table-total\">\n<td></td><td></td>\n<td><strong>Total</strong></td>\n<td><strong>3677</strong></td>\n<td><strong>0</strong></td>\n<td><strong>66</strong></td>\n<td><span class=\"tag tag-met\">PASS</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<div class=\"help-info-box mt-md\">\n<strong>About the 66 Warnings:</strong> \nWarnings are informational only and do not indicate defects in the scanner&rsquo;s \ntraceability chain. All 10 QA checks passed with <strong>zero errors</strong>. \nThe warnings fall into two categories:\n<ul style=\"margin:8px 0 0 0;padding-left:20px;\">\n<li><strong>Method Mapping (1):</strong> \nCheck definitions exist in config but are not yet wired to scanner methods. \nThese checks appear as &ldquo;Manual Review Required&rdquo; at runtime until implementation is added.</li>\n<li><strong>Expected Condition Match (34):</strong> \nA heuristic text comparison between config <code>expected</code> fields (written in compliance language) \nand Python source code (written in SDK/API terms). Low keyword overlap is normal because the config \ndescribes <em>what</em> is validated while the code implements <em>how</em> via cloud APIs. \nThe API Call Match check (QA 2.1) independently verified all API calls are correct.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"card mb-lg\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<h3 class=\"help-section-title\">Cloud Provider Coverage</h3>\n<p class=\"help-section-desc\">\nThe scanner implements checks across all three major cloud service providers. \nAll 100 automated controls have checks for AWS, Azure, and GCP \nwith zero provider parity gaps.\n</p>\n<div class=\"help-stats-grid\">\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"aws\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">203</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">AWS</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">checks</div></div>\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"azure\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">147</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">Azure</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">checks</div></div>\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"gcp\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">146</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">GCP</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">checks</div></div>\n<div class=\"help-stat-card\" data-stat=\"total\"><div class=\"help-stat-value\">496</div><div class=\"help-stat-label\">Total</div><div class=\"help-stat-sublabel\">across 3 CSPs</div></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"help-info-box mt-md\">\n<strong>Provider Parity:</strong> \nQA check 1.8 verified that all 100 automated controls have check definitions \nfor every cloud provider. This means a client receives equivalent assessment coverage whether \ntheir environment runs on AWS, Azure, or GCP.\n</div>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"card mb-lg\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<h3 class=\"help-section-title\">Assurance for Assessors</h3>\n<p class=\"help-section-desc\">\nThis validation provides the following assurances to FedRAMP Assessors (3PAOs) \nevaluating the scanner as an automated assessment tool:\n</p>\n<div class=\"help-info-box mt-md\" style=\"border-left-color:#059669;\">\n<strong><span class=\"tag tag-met\" style=\"margin-right:6px;\">Verified</span> Every documented check has a real implementation</strong>\n<p style=\"margin:6px 0 0 0;\">QA checks 1.4 and 1.5 verify that every check_id in the config JSON is wired to an actual Python method in the scanner. There are no &ldquo;dead&rdquo; check definitions that claim to test something but have no code behind them.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"help-info-box mt-md\" style=\"border-left-color:#059669;\">\n<strong><span class=\"tag tag-met\" style=\"margin-right:6px;\">Verified</span> Every scanner method is registered and callable</strong>\n<p style=\"margin:6px 0 0 0;\">QA check 1.5 parses the scanner source code with Python&rsquo;s AST module to confirm that every method name in the engine&rsquo;s dispatch table exists as a real method in the scanner class. No method references dangle.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"help-info-box mt-md\" style=\"border-left-color:#059669;\">\n<strong><span class=\"tag tag-met\" style=\"margin-right:6px;\">Verified</span> Every cloud API call matches what&rsquo;s documented</strong>\n<p style=\"margin:6px 0 0 0;\">QA check 2.1 extracts actual API calls from each scanner method (following delegation chains up to 2 levels deep) and fuzzy-matches them against the <code>api_call</code> field in the config. The scanner calls exactly the APIs it documents.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"help-info-box mt-md\" style=\"border-left-color:#059669;\">\n<strong><span class=\"tag tag-met\" style=\"margin-right:6px;\">Verified</span> Every NIST 800-53 Rev 5 base control is covered</strong>\n<p style=\"margin:6px 0 0 0;\">QA check 1.7 verifies that all base NIST SP 800-53 Rev 5 controls appear in the check configuration  - either as automated checks or as manual-only entries. No base control is omitted from the scanner&rsquo;s scope.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"help-info-box mt-md\" style=\"border-left-color:#059669;\">\n<strong><span class=\"tag tag-met\" style=\"margin-right:6px;\">Verified</span> Every assessment objective is addressed</strong>\n<p style=\"margin:6px 0 0 0;\">QA check 1.3 verifies that every automatable 800-53A assessment objective is either covered by an automated check&rsquo;s <code>supports_objectives</code> list or flagged as requiring documentation. No blind spots exist in the objective-level coverage.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"help-info-box mt-md\" style=\"border-left-color:#059669;\">\n<strong><span class=\"tag tag-met\" style=\"margin-right:6px;\">Verified</span> The validation is reproducible</strong>\n<p style=\"margin:6px 0 0 0;\">This entire validation is a Python script that performs purely static analysis  - no cloud credentials, no running services, no network access required. Any assessor can re-run it and independently verify the results.</p>\n</div>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"card mb-lg\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<h3 class=\"help-section-title\">How to Reproduce This Validation</h3>\n<p class=\"help-section-desc\">\nAssessors can independently re-run this validation at any time. The script performs \npurely static analysis of config files and Python source code  - no cloud credentials, \ndatabase, or running services are needed.\n</p>\n<div class=\"help-cli-block\">\n<pre class=\"help-cli-pre\"># From the FedRAMP-SCANNER project root\ncd backend &amp;&amp; python ../scripts/qa_traceability.py</pre>\n</div>\n<p class=\"help-section-desc mt-md\">\nThe script will:\n</p>\n<ol style=\"margin:0;padding-left:20px;line-height:1.8;\">\n<li>Load all 2068 NIST controls from <code>config/nist_800_53_controls.json</code></li>\n<li>Load all check definitions from <code>config/checks/*.json</code> (20 domain files)</li>\n<li>Parse <code>engine.py</code> to extract <code>*_CHECK_METHODS</code> dispatch tables</li>\n<li>Parse all three scanner files (<code>aws_scanner.py</code>, <code>azure_scanner.py</code>, <code>gcp_scanner.py</code>) with Python AST analysis</li>\n<li>Run all 10 QA checks and output results to console and <code>qa/qa_traceability_report.md</code></li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"help-info-box mt-md\">\n<strong>Source files analyzed:</strong> \n<code>config/nist_800_53_controls.json</code>, \n<code>config/checks/*.json</code> (14 files), \n<code>backend/app/scanner/engine.py</code>, \n<code>backend/app/scanner/aws_scanner.py</code>, \n<code>backend/app/scanner/azure_scanner.py</code>, \n<code>backend/app/scanner/gcp_scanner.py</code>\n</div>\n</div></div>";
